710205f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, west side, from West 49th (left), to 50th (right) Street's, showing the Eighth Avenue Railroad car-barn prior to demolition and the site cleared for the new Madison Square Garden. Note the billboards on the 50th Street side announcing the Circus at the still employed old Garden on Madison Avenue and 26th Street.
Prior to 1926
